One of the annoying things with <a href="https://github.com/facebook/jest/">Jest</a> is that while it enables you to run only a single test by using <code>it.only</code>, it does not report this in any noticeable way. Thus you can end up in the same situation as we did, not running many tests without knowing it. (Oh yeah, if we only did review the code properly ...).<br><br>This git pre-commit hook will fail when you introduceÂ <code>it.only</code> into the code:<div id="gist20800593" class="gist">
